-- Intesa Sanpaolo takes 8.6 bln euros of ECB's targeted loans
-- 
-- Thu Dec 11, 2014 06:44AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 11 (Reuters) - Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> took 8.59 billion euros ($10.7 billion) in cheap funds the European Central Bank offered on Thursday under its second targeted longer-term refinancing operation this year, the Italian bank said in a statement.

